article.description: — Monty Scott scored 28 points as Eastern Michigan edged past Illinois State 103-98 in double overtime on Friday night.
article.headline: Scott leads E. Michigan past Illinois St. 103-98 in 2OT
article.linkText: Scott leads E. Michigan past Illinois St. 103-98 in 2OT
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- — Monty Scott scored 28 points as Eastern Michigan edged past Illinois State 103-98 in double overtime on Friday night. Bryce McBride added 23 points for the Eagles. McBride also had eight rebounds. Noah Farrakhan had 17 points and six rebounds for Eastern Michigan (1-1). Colin Golson Jr. added 16 points and seven rebounds. Antonio Reeves scored a career-high 32 points for the Redbirds (1-1). Sy Chatman scored a career-high 29 points plus 13 rebounds and four blocks.
